{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "3a6a1829-6af5-4d98-bcd8-f88e8913b01e",
    "name": "Employee Management API",
    "description": "This Postman collection contains the available endpoints for interacting with the Employee Management API.\n\nThe API provides functionality to manage employees, authentication, and system health monitoring.\n\n## Features\n\n- Employee CRUD operations\n    \n- Authentication with JWT\n    \n- Role-based authorization\n    \n- Department employee queries\n    \n- Health monitoring endpoint\n    \n\n## Authentication\n\nThe API uses **JWT Bearer authentication**.\n\nTo authenticate:\n\n1. Execute the **Login** request.\n    \n2. The access token will automatically be stored in the `Bearer` collection variable.\n    \n3. All other endpoints will automatically use this token.\n    \n\n## Roles\n\nTwo roles exist in the system:\n\nAdmin\n\n- Full access to all endpoints\n    \n\nUser\n\n- Read-only access to employee endpoints\n    \n\n## Base URL\n\n[https://localhost:7183/api/v1](https://localhost:7183/api/v1)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "6363575"
  },
